zql> bo<TAB>      --> becomes "book |" (cursor at end)
zql> bo<TAB>.title --> becomes "book.title |" (space removed)

-- After existing text
zql> SELECT * FROM bo<TAB> WHERE --> becomes "SELECT * FROM book | WHERE"

-- Multiple punctuations
zql> SELECT bo<TAB>,au<TAB> FROM |
zql> SELECT bo<TAB>,au<TAB>.name FROM | 
```

This solution automatically removes trailing whitespace when typing '.' or ',' and positions the cursor correctly after the punctuation character.

