To solve the problem of downcasting any `List` (`Vec<T>`) or `Option<T>` in Rust without duplicating code for each inner type, we can define a set of traits (`AnyList`, `AnyOption`, and `AnyEnum`) to handle containers and enums generically. These traits allow us to dynamically interact with containers and enums through trait objects, enabling recursive downcasting of their inner types. Here's the implementation:

### Solution Code

**Cargo.toml:**
```toml
[package]
name = "downcast_example"
version = "0.1.0"
edition = "2021"

[dependencies]
egui = "0.24.0"
eframe = "0.24.0"
```

**main.rs:**
```rust
use std::any::Any;
use std::fmt::Display;
use egui::{Ui, Color32, RichText, CollapsingHeader};

// Custom types for demonstration
#[derive(Clone, Default)]
pub enum DataType {
    #[default]
    Int,
    Float,
    Text,
}

#[derive(Clone, Default)]
pub enum ValueType {
    #[default]
    Scalar,
    Vector,
}

#[derive(Clone, Default)]
pub struct NamedTypeValue {
    pub name: String,
    pub value: ValueType,
}

#[derive(Clone, Default)]
pub struct ArgumentNamedValue {
    pub arg: String,
    pub value: DataType,
}

// Trait for any list (Vec<T>)
trait AnyList: Any {
    fn len(&self) -> usize;
    fn push_box(&mut self, value: Box<dyn Any>);
    fn remove(&mut self, index: usize);
    fn as_any_mut(&mut self, index: usize) -> Option<&mut dyn Any>;
    fn is_empty(&self) -> bool;
}

impl<T: 'static + Default + Clone> AnyList for Vec<T> {
    fn len(&self) -> usize {
        self.len()
    }

    fn push_box(&mut self, value: Box<dyn Any>) {
        if let Ok(value) = value.downcast::<T>() {
            self.push(*value);
        }
    }

    fn remove(&mut self, index: usize) {
        self.remove(index);
    }

    fn as_any_mut(&mut self, index: usize) -> Option<&mut dyn Any> {
        self.get_mut(index).map(|item| item as &mut dyn Any)
    }

    fn is_empty(&self) -> bool {
        self.is_empty()
    }
}

// Trait for any Option<T>
trait AnyOption: Any {
    fn is_none(&self) -> bool;
    fn set_none(&mut self);
    fn get_or_insert_default(&mut self) -> &mut dyn Any;
}

impl<T: 'static + Default> AnyOption for Option<T> {
    fn is_none(&self) -> bool {
        self.is_none()
    }

    fn set_none(&mut self) {
        *self = None;
    }

    fn get_or_insert_default(&mut self) -> &mut dyn Any {
        self.get_or_insert_with(|| T::default())
    }
}

// Trait for any enum
trait AnyEnum: Any {
    fn variants(&self) -> Vec<&'static str>;
    fn set_variant(&mut self, variant_idx: usize);
    fn current_variant(&self) -> usize;
    fn as_any_mut(&mut self) -> &mut dyn Any;
}

impl<T: AnyEnum> AnyEnum for Option<T> {
    fn variants(&self) -> Vec<&'static str> {
        if let Some(inner) = self.as_ref() {
            inner.variants()
        } else {
            vec!["None"]
        }
    }

    fn set_variant(&mut self, variant_idx: usize) {
        if variant_idx == 0 {
            *self = None;
        } else if let Some(inner) = self.as_mut() {
            inner.set_variant(variant_idx - 1);
        }
    }

    fn current_variant(&self) -> usize {
        if self.is_none() {
            0
        } else {
            self.as_ref().unwrap().current_variant() + 1
        }
    }

    fn as_any_mut(&mut self) -> &mut dyn Any {
        self.as_mut().unwrap()
    }
}

macro_rules! impl_enum {
    ($($ty:ident { $($variant:ident),* }),*) => {
        $(
            impl AnyEnum for $ty {
                fn variants(&self) -> Vec<&'static str> {
                    vec![$(stringify!($variant)),*]
                }

                fn set_variant(&mut self, variant_idx: usize) {
                    *self = match variant_idx {
                        $(x if x == stringify!($variant).as_ptr() as usize => $ty::$variant,)*
                        _ => panic!("Invalid variant index"),
                    };
                }

                fn current_variant(&self) -> usize {
                    match self {
                        $($ty::$variant => stringify!($variant).as_ptr() as usize,)*
                    }
                }

                fn as_any_mut(&mut self) -> &mut dyn Any {
                    self
                }
            }
        )*
    };
}

impl_enum! {
    DataType { Int, Float, Text },
    ValueType { Scalar, Vector }
}

// Property rendering functions
pub fn downcast_property(ui: &mut Ui, title: &str, value_mut: &mut dyn Any, interactable: bool) {
    if let Some(string_v) = value_mut.downcast_mut::<String>() {
        string_property(ui, title, string_v, interactable);
    } else if let Some(int_v) = value_mut.downcast_mut::<i32>() {
        i_property(ui, title, int_v, interactable);
    } else if let Some(float_v) = value_mut.downcast_mut::<f32>() {
        f_property(ui, title, float_v, interactable);
    } else if let Some(usize_v) = value_mut.downcast_mut::<usize>() {
        i_property(ui, title, usize_v, interactable);
    } else if let Some(bool_v) = value_mut.downcast_mut::<bool>() {
        bool_property(ui, title, bool_v, interactable);
    } else if let Some(any_list) = value_mut.downcast_mut::<&mut dyn AnyList>() {
        list_property(ui, title, any_list, interactable);
    } else if let Some(any_opt) = value_mut.downcast_mut::<&mut dyn AnyOption>() {
        option_property(ui, title, any_opt, interactable);
    } else if let Some(any_enum) = value_mut.downcast_mut::<&mut dyn AnyEnum>() {
        enum_property(ui, title, any_enum, interactable);
    } else if let Some(named_type_value) = value_mut.downcast_mut::<NamedTypeValue>() {
        struct_property(ui, title, named_type_value, interactable);
    } else if let Some(argument_named_value) = value_mut.downcast_mut::<ArgumentNamedValue>() {
        struct_property(ui, title, argument_named_value, interactable);
    } else {
        ui.label(RichText::new(format!("Field {}: unknown type", title)).color(Color32::LIGHT_RED));
    }
}

fn string_property(ui: &mut Ui, title: &str, value: &mut String, interactable: bool) {
    ui.horizontal(|ui| {
        ui.label(title);
        if interactable {
            ui.text_edit_singleline(value);
        } else {
            ui.label(value);
        }
    });
}

fn i_property<T: Display + Into<f64> + Any>(ui: &mut Ui, title: &str, value: &mut T, interactable: bool) {
    ui.horizontal(|ui| {
        ui.label(title);
        if interactable {
            let mut val = (*value).into();
            if ui.add(egui::DragValue::new(&mut val)).changed() {
                *value = unsafe { std::mem::transmute_copy(&val) };
            }
        } else {
            ui.label(format!("{}", value));
        }
    });
}

fn f_property(ui: &mut Ui, title: &str, value: &mut f32, interactable: bool) {
    ui.horizontal(|ui| {
        ui.label(title);
        if interactable {
            ui.add(egui::DragValue::new(value));
        } else {
            ui.label(format!("{}", value));
        }
    });
}

fn bool_property(ui: &mut Ui, title: &str, value: &mut bool, interactable: bool) {
    ui.horizontal(|ui| {
        ui.label(title);
        if interactable {
            ui.checkbox(value, "");
        } else {
            ui.label(format!("{}", value));
        }
    });
}

fn struct_property<T: Any>(ui: &mut Ui, title: &str, value: &mut T, interactable: bool) {
    CollapsingHeader::new(title)
        .show(ui, |ui| {
            let value_mut = value as &mut dyn Any;
            downcast_property(ui, "Field", value_mut, interactable);
        });
}

pub fn list_property(ui: &mut Ui, title: &str, any_list: &mut dyn AnyList, interactable: bool) {
    CollapsingHeader::new(title)
        .default_open(true)
        .enabled(interactable)
        .show(ui, |ui| {
            ui.horizontal(|ui| {
                if ui.button("➕ Add").clicked() {
                    any_list.push_box(Box::new(()));
                }
            });

            let mut i = 0;
            while i < any_list.len() {
                ui.horizontal(|ui| {
                    if let Some(item) = any_list.as_any_mut(i) {
                        downcast_property(ui, "", item, interactable);
                    }
                    if ui.button("❌").on_hover_text("Remove").clicked() {
                        any_list.remove(i);
                    } else {
                        i += 1;
                    }
                });
            }
        });
}

pub fn option_property(ui: &mut Ui, title: &str, any_opt: &mut dyn AnyOption, interactable: bool) {
    let mut is_none = any_opt.is_none();

    ui.horizontal(|ui| {
        ui.label(title);
        if interactable {
            ui.checkbox(&mut is_none, "None");
        } else {
            ui.label(format!("{}", is_none));
        }

        if is_none {
            any_opt.set_none();
        } else {
            let inner = any_opt.get_or_insert_default();
            downcast_property(ui, "", inner, interactable);
        }
    });
}

fn enum_property(ui: &mut Ui, title: &str, any_enum: &mut dyn AnyEnum, interactable: bool) {
    let variants = any_enum.variants();
    let current_idx = any_enum.current_variant();

    ui.horizontal(|ui| {
        ui.label(title);
        if interactable {
            egui::ComboBox::from_id_source(title)
                .selected_text(variants[current_idx])
                .show_ui(ui, |ui| {
                    for (idx, variant) in variants.iter().enumerate() {
                        if ui.selectable_value(&mut current_idx, idx, *variant).clicked() {
                            any_enum.set_variant(idx);
                        }
                    }
                });
        } else {
            ui.label(variants[current_idx]);
        }
    });
}

// Example UI
struct TestData {
    a_string: String,
    an_int: i32,
    a_float: f32,
    a_bool: bool,
    a_data_type: DataType,
    an_option: Option<String>,
    a_vec: Vec<f32>,
    named_value: NamedTypeValue,
    arg_value: ArgumentNamedValue,
}

impl Default for TestData {
    fn default() -> Self {
        Self {
            a_string: "Hello".to_string(),
            an_int: 42,
            a_float: 3.14,
            a_bool: true,
            a_data_type: DataType::Float,
            an_option: Some("Option".to_string()),
            a_vec: vec![1.0, 2.0, 3.0],
            named_value: NamedTypeValue::default(),
            arg_value: ArgumentNamedValue::default(),
        }
    }
}

struct App {
    test_data: TestData,
}

impl App {
    fn new() -> Self {
        Self {
            test_data: TestData::default(),
        }
    }
}

impl eframe::App for App {
    fn update(&mut self, ctx: &egui::Context, _frame: &mut eframe::Frame) {
        egui::CentralPanel::default().show(ctx, |ui| {
            downcast_property(ui, "a_string", &mut self.test_data.a_string, true);
            downcast_property(ui, "an_int", &mut self.test_data.an_int, true);
            downcast_property(ui, "a_float", &mut self.test_data.a_float, true);
            downcast_property(ui, "a_bool", &mut self.test_data.a_bool, true);
            downcast_property(ui, "a_data_type", &mut self.test_data.a_data_type, true);
            downcast_property(ui, "an_option", &mut self.test_data.an_option, true);
            downcast_property(ui, "a_vec", &mut self.test_data.a_vec, true);
            downcast_property(ui, "named_value", &mut self.test_data.named_value, true);
            downcast_property(ui, "arg_value", &mut self.test_data.arg_value, true);
        });
    }
}

fn main() {
    let options = eframe::NativeOptions::default();
    eframe::run_native(
        "Downcast Example",
        options,
        Box::new(|_cc| Box::new(App::new())),
    );
}
```

### Explanation

1. **Traits for Container Handling**:
   - `AnyList`: Provides methods for interacting with any `Vec<T>` as a list of `dyn Any` elements.
   - `AnyOption`: Allows dynamic handling of `Option<T>` by checking/setting `None` and accessing the inner value.
   - `AnyEnum`: Enables dynamic enum handling by listing variants and setting values.

2. **Macro for Enums**:
   - The `impl_enum!` macro implements `AnyEnum` for specified enums (`DataType`, `ValueType`), allowing dynamic variant selection.

3. **Downcast Function**:
   - The `downcast_property` function first checks for primitive types, then uses the traits to handle containers (`Vec<T>`, `Option<T>`) and enums dynamically without per-type duplication.

4. **GUI Integration**:
   - Property rendering functions (`string_property`, `i_property`, etc.) handle UI elements. The `list_property` and `option_property` functions use the traits to render containers recursively.

5. **Example App**:
   - A test struct (`TestData`) demonstrates various types. The `App` struct uses `downcast_property` to render editable properties in an `eframe` window.

This approach efficiently handles any `Vec<T>` or `Option<T>` by leveraging trait objects and recursive downcasting, eliminating code duplication for different inner types.

