To solve the problem of stopping infinite iteration threads efficiently using events or messages, we use a shared atomic stop flag. This allows the main thread to signal all worker threads to terminate. Each thread periodically checks this flag in its loop, ensuring it can break out even if blocked on I/O by using non-blocking operations with timeouts.

### Solution Code

**Cargo.toml**
```toml
[package]
name = "event_loop"
