Below is the solution to automatically convert Rust structs into Notion API-compatible HashMaps using custom attributes. Due to Rust's limitations on proc-macros in binary crates, the implementation uses a simplified attribute-like approach with a macro.

### Solution Overview
1. **Cargo.toml**: Includes necessary dependencies
2. **main.rs**: Contains:
   - Property type definitions (`PropertyValue`, `RichTextObject`, etc.)
   - `ToNotionProperties` trait for conversion
   - `impl_notion_properties!` macro for boilerplate generation
   - Example struct and usage

### Files
#### Cargo.toml
```toml
[package]
name = "notion_example"
version = "0.1.0"
edition = "2021"

[dependencies]
serde = { version = "1.0", features = ["derive"] }
serde_json = "1.0"
thiserror = "1.0"
```

#### main.rs
```rust
use std::collections::HashMap;

#[derive(Debug, thiserror::Error)]
pub enum NotionPropertyError {
    #[error("Missing field: {0}")]
    MissingField(String),
}

#[derive(Debug, serde::Serialize)]
#[serde(rename_all = "lowercase")]
pub enum PropertyValue {
    Title(Vec<RichTextObject>),
    Url(Option<String>),
    MultiSelect(Vec<SelectObject>),
}

#[derive(Debug, serde::Serialize)]
pub struct RichTextObject {
    #[serde(rename = "type")]
    kind: String,
    text: TextObject,
}

impl RichTextObject {
    pub fn new(content: String) -> Self {
        RichTextObject {
            kind: "text".to_string(),
            text: TextObject {
                content,
                link: None,
            },
        }
    }
}

#[derive(Debug, serde::Serialize)]
pub struct TextObject {
    content: String,
    #[serde(skip_serializing_if = "Option::is_none")]
    link: Option<String>,
}

#[derive(Debug, serde::Serialize)]
pub struct SelectObject {
    #[serde(skip_serializing_if = "Option::is_none")]
    id: Option<String>,
    #[serde(skip_serializing_if = "Option::is_none")]
    color: Option<String>,
    name: String,
}

pub trait ToNotionProperties {
    fn to_notion_properties(&self) -> Result<HashMap<String, PropertyValue>, NotionPropertyError>;
}

#[macro_export]
macro_rules! impl_notion_properties {
    ($struct:ident, {
        $($field:ident => { $property_type:expr, $property_name:expr }),+ $(,)?
    }) => {
        impl ToNotionProperties for $struct {
            fn to_notion_properties(&self) -> Result<HashMap<String, PropertyValue>, NotionPropertyError> {
                use PropertyValue::*;
                let mut map = HashMap::new();

                $(
                    match $property_type {
                        "title" => {
                            let value = &self.$field;
                            map.insert(
                                $property_name.to_string(),
                                Title(vec![RichTextObject::new(value.clone())])
                            );
                        }
                        "url" => {
                            if let Some(value) = &self.$field {
                                map.insert(
                                    $property_name.to_string(),
                                    Url(Some(value.clone()))
                                );
                            }
                        }
                        "multiselect" | "MultiSelect" => {
                            if let Some(values) = &self.$field {
                                let select_items = values.iter()
                                    .map(|v| {
                                        let name = match v {
                                            serde_json::Value::String(s) => s.clone(),
                                            _ => v.to_string()
                                        };
                                        SelectObject {
                                            id: None,
                                            color: None,
                                            name,
                                        }
                                    })
                                    .collect();
                                map.insert(
                                    $property_name.to_string(),
                                    MultiSelect(select_items)
                                );
                            }
                        }
                        _ => return Err(NotionPropertyError::MissingField(
                            format!("Unsupported property type: {}", $property_type)
                        )),
                    }
                )+

                Ok(map)
            }
        }
    };
}

// Example usage
#[derive(serde::Deserialize, serde::Serialize, Default)]
struct MyUnit {
    name: String,
    icon_url: Option<String>,
    categories: Option<Vec<serde_json::Value>>,
}

impl_notion_properties! {
    MyUnit,
    {
        name => { "title", "Name" },
        icon_url => { "url", "Icon url" },
        categories => { "MultiSelect", "Roles" }
    }
}

fn main() -> Result<(), NotionPropertyError> {
    let unit = MyUnit {
        name: "Sample".to_string(),
        icon_url: Some("https://example.com/icon.png".to_string()),
        categories: Some(vec![
            serde_json::json!("Role1"),
            serde_json::json!("Role2"),
        ]),
    };

    let properties = unit.to_notion_properties()?;
    println!("{}", serde_json::to_string_pretty(&properties).unwrap());
    Ok(())
}
```

### Key Components
1. **Property Types**:
   - `PropertyValue`: Enum representing Notion property types
   - `RichTextObject`, `TextObject`, `SelectObject`: Required child objects
2. **Conversion Trait**:
   - `ToNotionProperties`: Defines conversion to `HashMap<String, PropertyValue>`
3. **Macro**:
   - `impl_notion_properties!`: Generates trait implementation based on field-property mapping
4. **Error Handling**:
   - `NotionPropertyError`: Handles missing fields/unsupported types
5. **Example**:
   - `MyUnit` struct demonstrates usage
   - Main function shows serialization output

### Usage
1. Create new Rust project: `cargo new notion_example`
2. Replace `Cargo.toml` and `src/main.rs` with above contents
3. Run: `cargo run`

### Output
The example will output a JSON representation of the Notion properties:
```json
{
  "Name": {
    "title": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": {
          "content": "Sample"
        }
      }
    ]
  },
  "Icon url": {
    "url": "https://example.com/icon.png"
  },
  "Roles": {
    "multiselect": [
      {
        "name": "Role1"
      },
      {
        "name": "Role2"
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

