            last_tick = Instant::now();
        }
    }

    Ok(())
}

</code></pre>
<p>When you run this code, you will see that the &quot;Tick!&quot; message is only printed to the console after you press a key, which demonstrates the blocking issue I need to solve. I am looking for the standard Rust pattern to handle both the timed &quot;Tick!&quot; and the user input concurrently.</p>


