To address your concerns, I've refactored the code to use tuples for method arguments instead of structs, which aligns with how D-Bus methods expect multiple arguments. This approach avoids complex lifetime issues and type conversions. Here's the complete solution:

### Cargo.toml
```toml
[package]
name = "dbus_example"
version = "0.1.0"
edition = "2021"

[dependencies]
zbus = "3.0"
tokio = { version = "1.0", features = ["rt-multi-thread", "macros"] }
