To resolve the issue of the `#[no_mangle]` attribute triggering an "unsafe attribute" error when using a procedural macro on a struct, we need to generate the exported function within a separate module. This approach avoids the unsafe attribute error while maintaining the required function export.

Here's the complete solution:

### Cargo.toml
```toml
[package]
name = "driver_project"
version = "0.1.0"
edition = "2021"

[dependencies]
syn = { version = "2.0", features = ["full"] }
